OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FMs White said her partner did say he
OL,8,Ffelt supported by the fire service,
OL,9,Falthough Mr Sahota said Mr Brown was a
OL,10,F"private and stoic" man who did not
OL,11,Fseek the support from occupational
OL,12,Fhealth colleagues that he was urged to
OL,13,Ftake during their meetings.
OL,15,FOn one occasion days before he died,
OL,16,Fthe fire chief, who took up the role
OL,17,Fpermanently in April 2023, did tell Mr
OL,18,FSahota that he was feeling under
OL,19,Fpressure, was exhausted, struggling to
OL,20,Fsleep and had "racing thoughts".
