OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FMr Sahota told the inquest: "My view
OL,8,Fat the time was that he was saying he
OL,9,Fwas okay. I urged him to reach out to
OL,10,Foccupational health.
OL,12,F"I had to be careful with Wayne... I
OL,13,Fdidn't want to annoy him, it was quite
OL,14,Fclear he was private and he was the
OL,15,Fmost senior person in the organisation
OL,16,Fand I didn't want to be disrespectful
OL,17,Fof that because it would affect my
OL,18,Frelationship with him going forward."
